Projectiles live in either the player or enemy ship space.

SpaceManager::OnLoop checks if a projectile is outside the [-800,800] bounds
in either the x or y component.

If so, and it's headed to another space, it calls Projectile::EnterDestinationSpace.
(If it's not headed for another space, it missed and is destroyed.)

This calculates an entry position for this projectile (this can be set ahead
of time, for burst weapons to make them come in from the same angle).

It takes a random angle, and uses it to find a point in a ring of
radius 800*0.75 pixels around the point 200,200. This is the starting
position of this projectile in the new space.
